{"title_page": "Thao & the Get Down Stay Down", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Thao & the Get Down Stay Down\n| image = Music - Thao & The Get Down Stay Down - Prospect Park Bandshell - Celebrate Brooklyn (20478247416).jpg\n| caption = Performing at Prospect Park Bandshell, 2009\n| landscape = Yes\n| background = group_or_band\n| origin = [[Falls Church, Virginia]], United States\n| genre = [[Folk rock]], [[alternative rock]]\n| years_active = 2003\u2013present\n| label = Trust Me Corporation<br />[[Ribbon Music]]\n| website = [http://thaoandthegetdownstaydown.com/ Official website]\n| current_members = [[Thao Nguyen]]<br/>Adam Thompson<br/>Charlie Glenn<br/>Jason Slota<br/>Johanna Kunin\n| past_members = Willis Thompson<br/>Frank Stewart<br/>Lisa Schonberg\n}}\n'''Thao & the Get Down Stay Down''' is a [[San Francisco]]-based [[alternative rock|alternative]] [[folk rock]] music group that originated in [[Falls Church, Virginia]].  It consists of [[Thao Nguyen]] ([[singing|vocals]], [[guitar]]) and Adam Thompson ([[Singing|vocals]], [[bass guitar]], [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]]). Frank Stewart (lead guitar, [[record producer|production]]) and Willis Thompson ([[drum kit|drums]]) are former members of the band.\n\n==History==\nThao Nguyen met drummer Willis Thompson while studying for her degrees in Sociology and Women's Studies at [[College of William & Mary]].<ref>[http://blog.kexp.org/blog/2009/09/30/song-of-the-day-thao-with-the-get-down-stay-down-know-better-learn-faster/ Song of the Day: September 30, 2009 - Kexp.org] Retrieved 2011-01-25.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thao Nguyen's Women's Prison Work: The Painful, Inspiring Stories of Four Inmates|url=http://www.spinner.com/2013/03/07/thao-nguyen-womens-prison-essay/|website=Spinner.com|accessdate=17 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Singer-songwriter Thao Nguyen (Women\u2019s Studies, \u201906) releases her new album|url=http://www.wm.edu/as/womensstudies/news/singer-songwriter-thao-nguyen-womens-studies,-06-releases-her-new-album.php|publisher=College of William & Mary|accessdate=17 June 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513032420/https://www.wm.edu/as/womensstudies/news/singer-songwriter-thao-nguyen-womens-studies,-06-releases-her-new-album.php|archivedate=13 May 2011}}</ref> Willis Thompson was a member of Camp Tigerclaw, Acousticore, and Murphy's Kids. He is also a contributing member to the band The Light Footwork. Thao Nguyen and Willis Thompson met Adam Thompson (no relation) during a show at the Harrison Street Coffee Shop in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. At the time, Adam Thompson was performing as a solo jazz-influenced act under the moniker The OK Bird.  Frank Stewart, member of the bands Durian and Verbal, would produce the first album ''[[Like the Linen]]'' in 2005 and join the band as a lead guitarist. Although only Willis and Nguyen initially performed live on tour, the four members began touring as a group during the [[Kill Rock Stars]]' Sound the Hare Heard tour during the summer of 2006.  The name of the band was originally suggested by a former bassist of the band.  Nguyen would expand the initial suggestion of \"The Get Down\" to \"The Get Down Stay Down\". Thao Nguyen still occasionally performs as a soloist, including a European tour with [[Laura Veirs]] and the Tortured Souls in August 2006.\n\nAfter sending ''Like the Linen'' to Laura Veirs, Thao was able to get connected to [[Tucker Martine]], Veirs' drummer and producer for [[The Decemberists]] and [[Sufjan Stevens]]. In August 2006, the group began recording with Martine in Seattle and released the album, ''[[We Brave Bee Stings and All]]'', in January 2008. Thao Nguyen has since moved to [[San Francisco]], [[California]]. The band toured in 2008 with [[Xiu Xiu]], and separately with [[Rilo Kiley]] before heading out on their first headlining tour that summer.<ref>{{cite web|last=Katzif |first=Mike |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94282059 |title=Thao Nguyen: Tiny Desk Concert |website=Npr.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-04}}</ref>\n\nThao & the Get Down Stay Down released their second album, ''[[Know Better Learn Faster]]'', on October 13, 2009. Thao was joined by [[Andrew Bird]] on the title track. The band toured the US with [[The Portland Cello Project]] and David Shultz and the Skyline in late 2009, and spent time touring the US and Europe in Winter/Spring 2010.\n\nIn early 2010, Nguyen collaborated with [[Mirah]], culminating in a collaborative album.\n\nThe band's track \"When We Swam\" is the opening theme for Australian prime-time TV series ''[[Offspring (TV series)|Offspring]]'' (which premiered in Australia in August 2010).\n\nThe band also composed and performed the soundtrack for the 2011 film, ''American Teacher''.<ref>{{cite web|title=American Teacher Soundtrack|url=http://differentfurstudios.com/blog/?p=4948|publisher=Different Fur Studios|website=Differentfurstudios.com|accessdate=6 July 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725163220/http://differentfurstudios.com/blog/?p=4948|archivedate=25 July 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn October 25, 2012, [[Ribbon Music]] announced Nguyen signed with the label for the release of her new album entitled, ''[[We the Common]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=RIBBON RELEASE NEW THAO & THE GET DOWN STAY DOWN ALBUM IN FEBRUARY|url=http://www.dominorecordco.com/uk/news/25-10-12/ribbon-release-new-thao--the-get-down-stay-down-album-in-february/|website=Dominorecordco.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> and unveiled the first single \"Holy Roller\" via [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down \u2013 \"Holy Roller\"|url=http://stereogum.com/1184271/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-holy-roller/news/|website=Stereogum.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thao And The Get Down Stay Down Tease New Album|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/allsongs/2012/10/25/163621025/thao-and-the-get-down-stay-down-tease-new-album?ft=1&f=|website=Npr.org|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> The album, released on February 5, 2013,<ref>{{cite web|title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down's New Album \"We The Common\" Out February 5th|url=http://www.pluginmusic.com/news/article/thao-amp-the-get-down-stay-downs-new-album-we-the-common-out-february-5th|website=Pluginmusic.com|accessdate=1 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down Announce \"We The Common\" Out February 5 Via Ribbon Music|url=http://www.undertheradarmag.com/news/thao_the_get_down_stay_down_announce_we_the_common/|website=Undertheradarmag.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> features 12 tracks including a collaboration with indie songstress [[Joanna Newsom]] on \"Kindness Be Conceived\", Nguyen and Newsom having met at a songwriters' retreat.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hear Thao & the Get Down Stay Down's Spirited 'Holy Roller'|url=https://www.spin.com/2012/10/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-holy-roller/|website=Spin.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Studarus\">Studarus, Laura (2013) \"[http://www.pastemagazine.com/blogs/lists/2013/12/the-10-best-musical-collaborations-of-2013.html The 10 Best Musical Collaborations of 2013]\", ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'', December 22, 2013. Retrieved January 4, 2014</ref><ref name=\"Lao\">Lao, Melody (2013) \"[http://exclaim.ca/News/thao_nguyen_talks_sound_of_we_people_her_joanna_newsom_collab_rapping Thao Nguyen Talks the Sound of 'We the Common,' Her Joanna Newsom Collab, and... Rapping?]\", ''[[Exclaim!]]'', January 29, 2013. Retrieved January 4, 2014</ref> This time around, she says, her album is \"a lot less about my problems and more about how I could be a better participant in my life. There's a sense of revival and gratitude throughout the record that adds to this vitality of it.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lau |first=Melody |url=http://exclaim.ca/Interviews/WebExclusive/thao_get_down_stay_down-we_common_2 |title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down We the Common |website=Exclaim.ca |date=2013-02-06 |accessdate=2016-06-04}}</ref> As part of the promotional tour for the album, Thao & the Get Down Stay Down joined the lineup of numerous music festivals, including 2013's [[South by Southwest]] and [[Outside Lands Music and Arts Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Paul McCartney, Nine Inch Nails, Phoenix, Yeah Yeah Yeahs Heading to Outside Lands 2013|url=https://www.spin.com/2013/04/outside-lands-2013-lineup/|website=Spin.com|accessdate=27 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Featured Artist: Thao and The Get Down Stay Down|url=http://sxsw.com/sxsw-fm/news/featured-artist-thao-and-get-down-stay-down|website=Sxsw.com|accessdate=27 April 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130427114610/http://sxsw.com/sxsw-fm/news/featured-artist-thao-and-get-down-stay-down|archivedate=27 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013 the band released an [[Extended play|EP]], ''The Feeling Kind'', which included [[cover version]]s of songs by [[Melanie Safka|Melanie]], [[the Troggs]], and [[Yo La Tengo]].<ref>Bowe, Miles (2013) \"[http://www.stereogum.com/1554672/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-the-feeling-kind-video-stereogum-premiere/video/ Thao & The Get Down Stay Down \u2013 \u201cThe Feeling Kind\u201d Video (Stereogum Premiere)]\", Stereogum.com, November 6, 2013. Retrieved January 4, 2014</ref>\n\nThao & the Get Down Stay Down released their fourth studio album, ''[[A Man Alive]]'', on March 4, 2016. The album was produced by [[Merrill Garbus]], who also produced Thao and Mirah's collaborative album, ''[[Thao + Mirah]]''.<ref name=\"Primas\">{{cite web|url=http://www.7x7.com/culture/thao-get-down-stay-down-drops-new-album-set-play-fillmore |title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down Drops New Album, Set to Play the Fillmore |website=7x7.com |date=2016-02-18 |accessdate=2016-06-04}}</ref>\n\n== Band members ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Current\n* [[Thao Nguyen]] &ndash; lead vocals, [[electric guitar|guitar]], [[banjo]], [[piano]] <small>(2003\u2013present)</small>\n* Adam Thompson &ndash; [[bass guitar|bass]], [[piano]], [[electric guitar|guitar]] <small>(2003\u2013present)</small>\n* Charlie Glenn &ndash; [[electric guitar|guitar]], [[piano]] <small>(2010\u2013present)</small>\n* Jason Slota &ndash; [[drums]] <small>(2010\u2013present)</small>\n* Johanna Kunin &ndash; [[piano]], [[backing vocals]] <small>(2014\u2013present)</small>\n\n{{col-2}}\n;Former\n* Willis Thompson &ndash; [[drums]] <small>(2003\u20132010)</small>\n* Frank Stewart &ndash; [[electric guitar|guitar]], [[piano]] <small>(2005\u20132008)</small>\n* Lisa Schonberg &ndash; [[drums]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Timeline===\n{{#tag:timeline|\nImageSize = width:800 height:auto barincrement:20\nPlotArea = left:130 bottom:120 top:0 right:20\nAlignbars = justify\nDateFormat = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod = from:01/01/2003 till:{{#time:m/d/Y}}\nTimeAxis = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\nLegend = orientation:vertical position:bottom columns:4\nScaleMajor = increment:2 start:2003\nScaleMinor = increment:1 start:2003\n\nColors =\n  id:Vocals  value:red     legend:Vocals\n  id:Guitar  value:green   legend:Guitar\n  id:Bass    value:blue    legend:Bass\n  id:Drums   value:orange  legend:Drums\n  id:Keys    value:purple  legend:Keys\n  id:Lines   value:black   legend:Studio_albums\n\nLineData =\n  at:06/01/2005  color:black  layer:back\n  at:01/28/2008  color:black  layer:back\n  at:10/13/2009  color:black  layer:back\n  at:02/05/2013  color:black  layer:back\n  at:03/04/2016  color:black  layer:back\n\nBarData =\n bar:Nguyen        text:\"Thao Nguyen\"\n\n bar:Stewart       text:\"Frank Stewart\"\n bar:Glenn         text:\"Charlie Glenn\"\n\n bar:Kunin         text:\"Johanna Kunin\"\n\n bar:AThompson     text:\"Adam Thompson\"\n\n bar:WThompson     text:\"Willis Thompson\"\n bar:Slota         text:\"Jason Slota\"\n\nPlotData =\n  width:2.5 textcolor:black align:left anchor:from shift:(10,-4)\n bar:Nguyen      from:start      till:end        color:Vocals\n\n  width:10 textcolor:black align:left anchor:from shift:(10,-4)\n bar:Nguyen      from:start      till:end        color:Guitar\n bar:Stewart     from:01/01/2005 till:04/01/2008 color:Guitar\n bar:Glenn       from:08/01/2010 till:end        color:Guitar\n\n  width:2.5 textcolor:black align:left anchor:from shift:(10,-4)\n bar:Kunin      from:08/01/2010      till:end        color:Vocals\n\n  width:10 textcolor:black align:left anchor:from shift:(10,-4)\n bar:Kunin      from:08/01/2010      till:end        color:Keys\n\n bar:AThompson   from:start      till:end        color:Bass\n\n bar:WThompson   from:start      till:08/01/2010 color:Drums\n bar:Slota       from:08/01/2010 till:end        color:Drums\n}}\n\n==Discography==\n;Albums\n* ''[[We Brave Bee Stings and All]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Know Better Learn Faster]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[We the Common]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[A Man Alive]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Temple]]'' (2020)<ref>https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-temple-tour-dates/</ref>\n\n;EPs\n* ''The Feeling Kind'' (2013), Ribbon Music\n\n;Singles\n* \"Bag of Hammers\" from ''[[We Brave Bee Stings and All]]''\n* \"Know Better Learn Faster\" from ''[[Know Better Learn Faster]]''\n* \"Holy Roller\" from ''[[We the Common]]''\n* \"The Feeling Kind\" from [[We the Common]]\n* \"An Astonished Man\" from [[A Man Alive]]\n\n;Compilation contributions\n* \"Feet Asleep\" \u2013 ''[[The Sound the Hare Heard]]'' (2006, [[Kill Rock Stars]] compilation disc)\n* \"Young Man\" \u2013 ''Kill Rock Stars Winter Holiday Album'' (2006, [[Kill Rock Stars]] compilation, digital release only)\n\n;Collaborations\n* ''Thao/The Thermals Record Store Day Split 7\"'' (2009) EP split with the Thermals, released for Record Store Day \u2013 April 18, 2009\n* ''The Thao and Justin Power Sessions'' (2009) with The Portland Cello Project\n* ''[[Thao + Mirah]]'' (2011) LP with [[Mirah]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Thao & the Get Down Stay Down}}\n*[http://thaoandthegetdownstaydown.com/ Official Website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thao and The Get Down Stay Down}}\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2003]]\n[[Category:American folk rock groups]]\n[[Category:Indie pop groups from Virginia]]\n[[Category:Indie pop groups from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:Feminist musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{more footnotes|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Thao & the Get Down Stay Down\n| image = Music - Thao & The Get Down Stay Down - Prospect Park Bandshell - Celebrate Brooklyn (20478247416).jpg\n| caption = Performing at Prospect Park Bandshell, 2009\n| landscape = Yes\n| background = group_or_band\n| origin = [[Falls Church, Virginia]], United States\n| genre = [[Folk rock]], [[alternative rock]]\n| years_active = 2003\u2013present\n| label = Trust Me Corporation<br />[[Ribbon Music]]\n| website = [http://thaoandthegetdownstaydown.com/ Official website]\n| current_members = [[Thao Nguyen]]<br/>Adam Thompson<br/>Charlie Glenn<br/>Jason Slota<br/>Johanna Kunin\n| past_members = Willis Thompson<br/>Frank Stewart<br/>Lisa Schonberg\n}}\n'''Thao & the Get Down Stay Down''' is a [[San Francisco]]-based [[alternative rock|alternative]] [[folk rock]] music group that originated in [[Falls Church, Virginia]].  It consists of [[Thao Nguyen]] ([[singing|vocals]], [[guitar]]) and Adam Thompson ([[Singing|vocals]], [[bass guitar]], [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]]). Frank Stewart (lead guitar, [[record producer|production]]) and Willis Thompson ([[drum kit|drums]]) are former members of the band.\n\n==History==\nThao Nguyen met drummer Willis Thompson while studying for her degrees in Sociology and Women's Studies at [[College of William & Mary]].<ref>[http://blog.kexp.org/blog/2009/09/30/song-of-the-day-thao-with-the-get-down-stay-down-know-better-learn-faster/ Song of the Day: September 30, 2009 - Kexp.org] Retrieved 2011-01-25.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thao Nguyen's Women's Prison Work: The Painful, Inspiring Stories of Four Inmates|url=http://www.spinner.com/2013/03/07/thao-nguyen-womens-prison-essay/|website=Spinner.com|accessdate=17 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Singer-songwriter Thao Nguyen (Women\u2019s Studies, \u201906) releases her new album|url=http://www.wm.edu/as/womensstudies/news/singer-songwriter-thao-nguyen-womens-studies,-06-releases-her-new-album.php|publisher=College of William & Mary|accessdate=17 June 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513032420/https://www.wm.edu/as/womensstudies/news/singer-songwriter-thao-nguyen-womens-studies,-06-releases-her-new-album.php|archivedate=13 May 2011}}</ref> Willis Thompson was a member of Camp Tigerclaw, Acousticore, and Murphy's Kids. He is also a contributing member to the band The Light Footwork. Thao Nguyen and Willis Thompson met Adam Thompson (no relation) during a show at the Harrison Street Coffee Shop in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. At the time, Adam Thompson was performing as a solo jazz-influenced act under the moniker The OK Bird.  Frank Stewart, member of the bands Durian and Verbal, would produce the first album ''[[Like the Linen]]'' in 2005 and join the band as a lead guitarist. Although only Willis and Nguyen initially performed live on tour, the four members began touring as a group during the [[Kill Rock Stars]]' Sound the Hare Heard tour during the summer of 2006.  The name of the band was originally suggested by a former bassist of the band.  Nguyen would expand the initial suggestion of \"The Get Down\" to \"The Get Down Stay Down\". Thao Nguyen still occasionally performs as a soloist, including a European tour with [[Laura Veirs]] and the Tortured Souls in August 2006.\n\nAfter sending ''Like the Linen'' to Laura Veirs, Thao was able to get connected to [[Tucker Martine]], Veirs' drummer and producer for [[The Decemberists]] and [[Sufjan Stevens]]. In August 2006, the group began recording with Martine in Seattle and released the album, ''[[We Brave Bee Stings and All]]'', in January 2008. Thao Nguyen has since moved to [[San Francisco]], [[California]]. The band toured in 2008 with [[Xiu Xiu]], and separately with [[Rilo Kiley]] before heading out on their first headlining tour that summer.<ref>{{cite web|last=Katzif |first=Mike |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94282059 |title=Thao Nguyen: Tiny Desk Concert |website=Npr.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-04}}</ref>\n\nThao & the Get Down Stay Down released their second album, ''[[Know Better Learn Faster]]'', on October 13, 2009. Thao was joined by [[Andrew Bird]] on the title track. The band toured the US with The [[Portland Cello Project]] and David Shultz and the Skyline in late 2009, and spent time touring the US and Europe in Winter/Spring 2010.\n\nIn early 2010, Nguyen collaborated with [[Mirah]], culminating in a collaborative album.\n\nThe band's track \"When We Swam\" is the opening theme for Australian prime-time TV series ''[[Offspring (TV series)|Offspring]]'' (which premiered in Australia in August 2010).\n\nThe band also composed and performed the soundtrack for the 2011 film, ''American Teacher''.<ref>{{cite web|title=American Teacher Soundtrack|url=http://differentfurstudios.com/blog/?p=4948|publisher=Different Fur Studios|website=Differentfurstudios.com|accessdate=6 July 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725163220/http://differentfurstudios.com/blog/?p=4948|archivedate=25 July 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn October 25, 2012, [[Ribbon Music]] announced Nguyen signed with the label for the release of her new album entitled, ''[[We the Common]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=RIBBON RELEASE NEW THAO & THE GET DOWN STAY DOWN ALBUM IN FEBRUARY|url=http://www.dominorecordco.com/uk/news/25-10-12/ribbon-release-new-thao--the-get-down-stay-down-album-in-february/|website=Dominorecordco.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> and unveiled the first single \"Holy Roller\" via [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down \u2013 \"Holy Roller\"|url=http://stereogum.com/1184271/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-holy-roller/news/|website=Stereogum.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thao And The Get Down Stay Down Tease New Album|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/allsongs/2012/10/25/163621025/thao-and-the-get-down-stay-down-tease-new-album?ft=1&f=|website=Npr.org|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> The album, released on February 5, 2013,<ref>{{cite web|title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down's New Album \"We The Common\" Out February 5th|url=http://www.pluginmusic.com/news/article/thao-amp-the-get-down-stay-downs-new-album-we-the-common-out-february-5th|website=Pluginmusic.com|accessdate=1 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down Announce \"We The Common\" Out February 5 Via Ribbon Music|url=http://www.undertheradarmag.com/news/thao_the_get_down_stay_down_announce_we_the_common/|website=Undertheradarmag.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> features 12 tracks including a collaboration with indie songstress [[Joanna Newsom]] on \"Kindness Be Conceived\", Nguyen and Newsom having met at a songwriters' retreat.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hear Thao & the Get Down Stay Down's Spirited 'Holy Roller'|url=https://www.spin.com/2012/10/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-holy-roller/|website=Spin.com|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Studarus\">Studarus, Laura (2013) \"[http://www.pastemagazine.com/blogs/lists/2013/12/the-10-best-musical-collaborations-of-2013.html The 10 Best Musical Collaborations of 2013]\", ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'', December 22, 2013. Retrieved January 4, 2014</ref><ref name=\"Lao\">Lao, Melody (2013) \"[http://exclaim.ca/News/thao_nguyen_talks_sound_of_we_people_her_joanna_newsom_collab_rapping Thao Nguyen Talks the Sound of 'We the Common,' Her Joanna Newsom Collab, and... Rapping?]\", ''[[Exclaim!]]'', January 29, 2013. Retrieved January 4, 2014</ref> This time around, she says, her album is \"a lot less about my problems and more about how I could be a better participant in my life. There's a sense of revival and gratitude throughout the record that adds to this vitality of it.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lau |first=Melody |url=http://exclaim.ca/Interviews/WebExclusive/thao_get_down_stay_down-we_common_2 |title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down We the Common |website=Exclaim.ca |date=2013-02-06 |accessdate=2016-06-04}}</ref> As part of the promotional tour for the album, Thao & the Get Down Stay Down joined the lineup of numerous music festivals, including 2013's [[South by Southwest]] and [[Outside Lands Music and Arts Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Paul McCartney, Nine Inch Nails, Phoenix, Yeah Yeah Yeahs Heading to Outside Lands 2013|url=https://www.spin.com/2013/04/outside-lands-2013-lineup/|website=Spin.com|accessdate=27 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Featured Artist: Thao and The Get Down Stay Down|url=http://sxsw.com/sxsw-fm/news/featured-artist-thao-and-get-down-stay-down|website=Sxsw.com|accessdate=27 April 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130427114610/http://sxsw.com/sxsw-fm/news/featured-artist-thao-and-get-down-stay-down|archivedate=27 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013 the band released an [[Extended play|EP]], ''The Feeling Kind'', which included [[cover version]]s of songs by [[Melanie Safka|Melanie]], [[the Troggs]], and [[Yo La Tengo]].<ref>Bowe, Miles (2013) \"[http://www.stereogum.com/1554672/thao-the-get-down-stay-down-the-feeling-kind-video-stereogum-premiere/video/ Thao & The Get Down Stay Down \u2013 \u201cThe Feeling Kind\u201d Video (Stereogum Premiere)]\", Stereogum.com, November 6, 2013. Retrieved January 4, 2014</ref>\n\nThao & the Get Down Stay Down released their fourth studio album, ''[[A Man Alive]]'', on March 4, 2016. The album was produced by [[Merrill Garbus]], who also produced Thao and Mirah's collaborative album, ''[[Thao + Mirah]]''.<ref name=\"Primas\">{{cite web|url=http://www.7x7.com/culture/thao-get-down-stay-down-drops-new-album-set-play-fillmore |title=Thao & The Get Down Stay Down Drops New Album, Set to Play the Fillmore |website=7x7.com |date=2016-02-18 |accessdate=2016-06-04}}</ref>\n\n== Band members ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Current\n* [[Thao Nguyen]] &ndash; lead vocals, [[electric guitar|guitar]], [[banjo]], [[piano]] <small>(2003\u2013present)</small>\n* Adam Thompson &ndash; [[bass guitar|bass]], [[piano]], [[electric guitar|guitar]] <small>(2003\u2013present)</small>\n* Charlie Glenn &ndash; [[electric guitar|guitar]], [[piano]] <small>(2010\u2013present)</small>\n* Jason Slota &ndash; [[drums]] <small>(2010\u2013present)</small>\n* Johanna Kunin &ndash; [[piano]], [[backing vocals]] <small>(2014\u2013present)</small>\n\n{{col-2}}\n;Former\n* Willis Thompson &ndash; [[drums]] <small>(2003\u20132010)</small>\n* Frank Stewart &ndash; [[electric guitar|guitar]], [[piano]] <small>(2005\u20132008)</small>\n* Lisa Schonberg &ndash; [[drums]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Timeline===\n{{#tag:timeline|\nImageSize = width:800 height:auto barincrement:20\nPlotArea = left:130 bottom:120 top:0 right:20\nAlignbars = justify\nDateFormat = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod = from:01/01/2003 till:{{#time:m/d/Y}}\nTimeAxis = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\nLegend = orientation:vertical position:bottom columns:4\nScaleMajor = increment:2 start:2003\nScaleMinor = increment:1 start:2003\n\nColors =\n  id:Vocals  value:red     legend:Vocals\n  id:Guitar  value:green   legend:Guitar\n  id:Bass    value:blue    legend:Bass\n  id:Drums   value:orange  legend:Drums\n  id:Keys    value:purple  legend:Keys\n  id:Lines   value:black   legend:Studio_albums\n\nLineData =\n  at:06/01/2005  color:black  layer:back\n  at:01/28/2008  color:black  layer:back\n  at:10/13/2009  color:black  layer:back\n  at:02/05/2013  color:black  layer:back\n  at:03/04/2016  color:black  layer:back\n\nBarData =\n bar:Nguyen  