a's ancient oasis city of Palmyra threatened in fighting|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-crisis-palmyra-idUSBRE9320HL20130403|accessdate=12 December 2016|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Peter Malcolm|last1=Holt|title=The Age of the Crusades: The Near East from the Eleventh Century to 1517|year= 2013|origyear=1986|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-87152-1|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Peter Malcolm|last1=Holt|title=Early Mamluk Diplomacy, 1260\u20131290: Treaties of Baybars and Qal\u0101w\u016bn with Christian Rulers|year= 1995|publisher=Brill|volume=12|series=Islamic History and Civilization. Studies and Texts|isbn=978-90-04-10246-0|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=George Fadlo|last=Hourani|title=Arab Seafaring in the Indian Ocean in Ancient and Early Medieval Times|editor-first=John |editor-last=Carswell|edition=expanded|origyear=1951|year= 1995|publisher=Princeton University Press|series= Khayats Oriental Reprints|volume=3 |isbn=978-0-691-00032-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Transnationalism in Ancient and Medieval Societies: The Role of Cross-Border Trade and Travel|first= Michael C.|last=Howard|publisher= McFarland|year=2012|isbn=978-0-7864-9033-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Arabia and the Arabs. From the Bronze Age to the Coming of Islam|first=Robert G.|last=Hoyland|publisher=Routledge|year=2001|isbn=978-0-415-19535-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first1=R. Stephen|last1=Humphreys|title=From Saladin to the Mongols: The Ayyubids of Damascus, 1193\u20131260|year= 1977|publisher=State University of New York Press|isbn=978-0-87395-263-7|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=Kam\u0101l al-D\u012bn \u02bbUmar ibn A\u1e25mad|last=Ibn al-\u02bbAd\u012bm|editor1-first=Suhayl|editor1-last=Zakk\u0101r|title= Bughyat al-\u1e6dalab f\u012b t\u0101r\u012bkh \u1e24alab|language= ar|origyear= 1262|year=1988|publisher=D\u0101r al-Fikr (\u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0643\u0631)|volume= 7|oclc=30968859|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=Ab\u016b Ya\u02bbl\u010